oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Olga Rychen
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The last of the native Swiss who founded Hohenwald. She was brought here as a needle threader for a loom at Kersheidt's Clothing Manufacturer. Kersheidt's Manufacturing, of New York City, established a lace factory in Hohenwald, TN and employed the local swiss immigrants. On the onset of World War I, the factory shifted its output to embroidering military emblems. The factory shut down following the end of the war.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
